  "text": "Once the reliability and stability of MEG are established for these tasks and patient groups, there must be a demonstration that a specific \"signature\" of AD has concurrent validity with other known biomarkers such as brain structural and cerebral metabolism (and amyloid imaging) (e.g., [CITATION_1] ). In addition, there should be predictive validity in that the presence of an abnormality identified by MEG should correlate with pathological changes in AD identified at autopsy.",
